## ✨ Overview

**Speak to Cure** is a voice-first mental wellness platform that listens, understands, and supports users using AI-driven technologies. From voice journaling and multilingual support to real-time condition predictions and doctor mapping — it's healing, reimagined.

---

## 🚀 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Description |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| **Frontend** | ![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React%20%2F%20Next.js-2023-blue?logo=react) | Responsive UI for web and tablets |
| **Database** | ![Firebase](https://img.shields.io/badge/Firebase-Realtime%20DB-FFCA28?logo=firebase) | Patient records, preferences, history |
| **Speech Interface** | ![Sarvam AI](https://img.shields.io/badge/Sarvam%20AI-STT%2FTTS%2FMultilingual-purple) | Voice input/output with multilingual support |
| **Mapping** | ![Leaflet.js](https://img.shields.io/badge/Leaflet.js-Doctor%20Locator-green?logo=leaflet) | Pin plotting and map rendering |
| **Communication** | ![Twilio](https://img.shields.io/badge/Twilio%20%2F%20SendGrid-Reports%20%26%20Alerts-ff6c6c?logo=twilio) | Secure report delivery to doctors |
| **Backend ML** | ![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-FastAPI%20%2F%20Flask-3776AB?logo=python) | Mental condition prediction engine |
| **Health ID** | ![QR Code](https://img.shields.io/badge/QR%20Tools-Health%20ID%20QR-blue?logo=qrcode) | Scan & generate patient health codes |

---

## 🔥 Features

- 🎤 **Voice-first Interaction** – Speak your thoughts, let AI understand
- 🌍 **Multilingual Support** – Built for global accessibility
- 🧠 **Condition Prediction** – AI-powered emotional insight engine
- 🗺️ **Doctor Locator** – Nearby specialists on an interactive map
- ✉️ **Secure Report Sharing** – Instantly send reports to professionals
- 🔐 **Health QR ID** – Your records, one scan away
- ☁️ **Firebase Integration** – Seamless cloud data management

---

## ⚙️ Getting Started

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/speak-to-cure.git
cd speak-to-cure

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install              # React frontend
pip install -r backend/requirements.txt  # Python backend

# 3. Start the development servers
npm run dev              # React / Next.js
python app.py            # Flask OR uvicorn main:app --reload (FastAPI)